---
import "@fontsource-variable/inter";
import Footer from "~/components/footer.astro";
import GoogleAnalytics from "~/components/google-analytics.astro";
import Header from "~/components/header.astro";
import LanguagePreference from "~/components/language-preference.astro";
import { DEFAULT_LOCALE } from "~/i18n/config";
import { buildPageData } from "~/i18n/page-data";
import "~/styles/index.css";

const { generator, site } = Astro;
const locale = DEFAULT_LOCALE;
const pageData = buildPageData(locale, site);
const { copy, languageOptions } = pageData;

const PAGE_TITLE = "SignalRGB Review – Features, Performance & Pricing";
const PAGE_DESCRIPTION =
  "Review of SignalRGB: powerful RGB controller with screen sync and a freemium model. We look at lighting quality, latency, resource usage and pay‑to‑access friction.";

const navItems = [
  { title: "Best Picks", url: "/#best-picks" },
  { title: "Reviews", url: "/reviews/" },
  { title: "Comparisons", url: "/comparisons/" },
  { title: "Guides", url: "/guides/" },
  { title: "Device Compatibility", url: "/compatibility/" },
  { title: "FAQ", url: "/faq/" },
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang={locale} class="h-full motion-safe:scroll-smooth" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <LanguagePreference locale={locale} />
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    {generator && <meta name="generator" content={generator} />}
    <title>{PAGE_TITLE}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={PAGE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <meta property="og:title" content={PAGE_TITLE} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta property="og:description" content={PAGE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <meta property="og:image" content={pageData.head.image} />
    <meta property="og:url" content={pageData.head.canonical} />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://best-rgb-controller.com/reviews/signalrgb-review/" />

    <GoogleAnalytics />
  </head>
  <body
    class="h-full overflow-x-hidden bg-default pt-24 text-default text-base selection:bg-secondary selection:text-white"
  >
    <Header
      navItems={navItems}
      locale={locale}
      navLabel={copy.nav.ariaLabel}
      openLabel={copy.nav.openLabel}
      closeLabel={copy.nav.closeLabel}
      languageLabel={copy.language.label}
      languageOptions={languageOptions}
    />

    <main class="px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
      <article class="mx-auto max-w-7xl space-y-8">
        <header class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-primary">
            Review – SignalRGB
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-balance text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
            SignalRGB Review – powerful RGB controller with a freemium model
          </h1>
          <p class="max-w-3xl text-sm text-offset sm:text-base">
            SignalRGB offers a feature‑rich RGB platform with advanced effects and screen‑sync
            modes. In this review we look at lighting quality, performance and the impact of its
            paid tiers on everyday usage.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-xl">
            Highlights
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-offset sm:text-base">
            <li>Strong screen‑sync and effect system.</li>
            <li>Plenty of presets and community‑style effects.</li>
            <li>Freemium model with some features and layouts behind a paywall.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-xl">
            Performance and experience
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-offset sm:text-base">
            In exchange for its visual polish, SignalRGB can be heavier on resources than simpler
            controllers. This is usually fine on modern gaming PCs, but users who care about
            absolute minimal background footprint may prefer lighter alternatives such as Skydimo
            or OpenRGB.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-xl">
            Pricing and pay‑to‑access concerns
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-offset sm:text-base">
            SignalRGB uses a free+paid model. The free tier can be enough for basic setups, but
            some advanced effects and layouts are restricted to paying users. Community discussions
            sometimes criticise how visible these pay‑to‑access elements are inside the UI.
          </p>
        </section>

        <footer class="border-t border-slate-700/60 pt-6 text-sm text-offset">
          <p>
            If you are primarily interested in screen sync, compare this review with our
            <a
              href="/comparisons/rgb-software-screen-sync/"
              class="ml-1 underline decoration-slate-500/60 decoration-dotted underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
            >
              dedicated screen‑sync comparison
            </a>
            and the
            <a
              href="/comparisons/skydimo-vs-signalrgb/"
              class="ml-1 underline decoration-slate-500/60 decoration-dotted underline-offset-2 hover:text-primary"
            >
              Skydimo vs SignalRGB
            </a>
            article.
          </p>
        </footer>
      </article>
    </main>

    <Footer linkLabels={copy.footer.links} />
  </body>
</html>


